channel.title: Projects on Edmund Goodman
channel.description: Recent content in Projects on Edmund Goodman

item.title: Rouse Research
item.description: In Sixth Form, I completed a research project titled “How effective are machine learning algorithms compared with traditional analytical techniques, with respect to playing abstract games”.

item.title: EES
item.description: In Sixth Form, I lead the software aspect of the school “Engineering Education Scheme” entry, building an autonomous tennis ball collecting robot to the help sports teachers.

item.title: iGEM Modelling
item.description: As part of the Warwick 2021 iGEM team, I lead the development of a custom computer simulation of how our proposed product would perform in the real world.

item.title: iGEM Wiki
item.description: As part of the Warwick 2021 iGEM team, I lead the development of the wiki website, which was the main way our work was assessed.
